<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870413-0027 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Westcorp</HL><DD> 04/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WCRPBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   WESTCORP, Orange, Calif., said its Western Financial Savings Bank unit asked the Federal Home Loan Bank Board to approve an offering of $75 million of subordinated debentures due 2002. The financial-services company said the unit will use proceeds for general purposes, including consumer loans, acquisitions and other investment opportunities. Westcorp also said the thrift will ask state and federal regulators for permission to count the proceeds in calculating its net worth. Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. will manage the offering. </TEXT></DOC>